text: Itterbeck in Bentheim in Lower Saxony is an old farming community that has developed into an independent community with almost 1,800 residents (2005). Itterbeck belongs to the Joint Community (Samtgemeinde) of Uelsen, whose administrative seat is in the like-named community. Itterbeck’s constituent communities (Ortsteile) are Itterbeck, Egge, Itterbeckermoor, Kleine Striepe, Balderhaarmoor, Itterbeckerdoose and Ratzel. ==References== ==Other websites== *Joint community’s webpage * Category:County of Bentheim (district)
